.Im MicroEmacs modes
.so me.tni
.TH view 2m
.XI view - "Read only"
.SH NAME
view \- Read only
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "view Mode"
.sp
\fB\&V\fR\& \- mode line letters.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B view
mode sets the buffer to read-only, disabling the ability to alter the contents
of the buffer. This mode is automatically  set for any files attributed with a
read-only status on the file system when read into \*(mE. Files loaded via
.Ht view-file 2
are also assigned \fB\&view\fR\& mode.
.PP
While in \fB\&view\fR\& mode, any attempt to alter the buffer contents  results in
the following message:-
.IP
.C "[Key Illegal in view Mode]"
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Hl "Operating Modes" Modes - ,
.Ht buffer-mode 2 ,
.Ht global-mode 2 ,
.Ht view-file 2 .
.ad
